## Harness Contract

This section declares project capabilities so the harness running Claude (e.g. Claude Code) knows how to behave for this project. The block below is machine-parseable: harness implementations should look for a fenced code block tagged `harness-contract` and consume its YAML body. Older harnesses that don't recognize the tag will render it as a normal code block — the section is backwards-compatible.

```harness-contract
# Task tracking
# When this project declares an external task tracker, the harness's built-in
# TaskCreate primitive should NOT be suggested or nudged toward — using both
# fragments the audit trail. The harness should suppress reminders that
# advertise the built-in primitives listed under suppress_builtin_reminders.
task_tracker:
  type: mcp
  namespace: {{MCP_NAMESPACE}}
  canonical_tools:
    - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__save_task
    - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__update_task_status
    - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__add_progress_log
    - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__search_tasks
  suppress_builtin_reminders:
    - TaskCreate
    - TaskUpdate

# Tool preload
# Tools the harness should warm at session start so the agent can call them
# without a ToolSearch round-trip. Project-author-curated — list the tools
# you actually reach for on this project. Derived per-project CLAUDE.md
# files MAY add or remove entries here based on what the project actually uses.
preload_tools:
  - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__load_session_state
  - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__save_session_state
  - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__save_task
  - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__update_task_status
  - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__add_progress_log
  - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__search_tasks
  - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__save_plan
  - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__get_plan
  - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__save_document
  - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__update_document
  - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__link_document
  - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__batch
  - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__parse_file_ast
  - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__analyze_file
  - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__lsp
  - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__lsp_workspace_symbols
  - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__search_code_context
  - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__recent_activity
  - mcp__{{MCP_NAMESPACE}}__unified_search
```

**Why this matters:** without this contract, the harness has to guess. It defaults to nudging the agent toward its built-in `TaskCreate` primitive even when the project has a richer external tracker, and it lazy-loads MCP tool schemas one ToolSearch round-trip at a time. Both behaviors are reasonable defaults for a fresh project but adversarial to a project that has already declared its workflow. The contract above lets the project author override those defaults declaratively, in a file the harness already reads on every turn.

**For projects without an MCP task tracker:** delete this entire section. The harness's default behavior (suggest `TaskCreate`, lazy-load tools via `ToolSearch`) is correct in that case.

